    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.67) and **Kyle Tucker** (77.10) leading the charge as our top-tier offensive anchors. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a lucrative matchup against Kochanowicz, where a 5.35 xERA and favorable wind conditions elevate his profile into elite territory. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** remains a mandatory start despite a 42% rain risk; his efficiency at the #2 spot and solid xwOBA metrics make him a high-floor producer even in suboptimal weather. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.77) round out our premier options, with **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** specifically benefiting from a massive platoon advantage against L\u00f3pez and **Jackson Merrill** enjoying a significant 14% park factor boost that drives his projection comfortably into the high-70s.\n\nThe most challenging decision today was the exclusion of **Marcell Ozuna**, who fell just short of the active roster with a 59.22 score. While **Marcell Ozuna** provides reliable power, his ceiling was tempered by a moderate matchup against Rocker, and the optimizer favored the higher efficiency scores of **Nolan Schanuel** and **Nasim Nunez**, the latter of whom is prioritized for his speed utility in our 5x5 format. We are also monitoring the 42% rain risk at both the **Kyle Tucker** and **Heliot Ramos** venues. **Heliot Ramos** is currently skating on thin ice with a 41.44 score, serving as a lower-tier play; should the weather outlook deteriorate, he is the primary candidate to be swapped for a bench bat like **Jacob Wilson** (51.01) to protect our plate appearance caps. **Gunnar Henderson** faces a tougher test today against Bubic, and with an elite holding pitcher limiting his stolen base upside, we are tempering expectations while remaining confident in his role at the top of the order.",
